                <head>232. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On July 1, 1953, <persName corresp="#p_RK_1">Kermit Roosevelt</persName> received
                    a communication that stated that the British Prime Minister “has approved the
                    plan. The Embassy will be informed by the Foreign Office who will also give the
                    Ambassador their views on an ‘acceptable oil settlement’.” The communication
                    then inquired into the status of the detailed plans yet to be completed by
                    officials of the Central Intelligence Agency. (Central Intelligence Agency,
                        <gloss target="#t_DDO_1">DDO</gloss> Files, Job 80–01701R, Box 3, Folder 7,
                    TPAJAX Vol. 1)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
